description:
Patreon

Get early access to build and test build, be able to try all epochs and test them by yourself on Patreon or contact me for support on Discord

Insutrctions

My advice is to start with posted images prompt.

Also, for each model, look on version description and on keywords on the right panel.

Enjoy!

If you'd like to support my efforts and have access to early and bleeding edge builds, please think about joining my Patreon: https://www.patreon.com/betterCuteAsians

modelVersions.name: Flamenco
modelVersions.description:
I decided to post full body images to show all the dress, but as you might already know SD its not really good in generating images that arent close to the viewer and creates distortions in those cases.

Hi-res fix might fix most of the posted images but my computer isnt strong enough to do it. I advice anyway to always use Hi-res fix with this model with the proper denoising strenght and i will wait some of you to post images of this model generated with this function.

modelVersions.name: Indian
modelVersions.description:
This model has a strong bias toward indian subject (it's not a case eheh) but feel free to try generating an Asian indian dancer :P

Also this model has very big problems in hand drawing as you will see. This is caused by the training images of indian dancer since the indian dance has very wierd hand poses that SD can't really understand. My advice is to generate images with this model till you find the one you like then inpaint the hands taking out the model from the prompt and hope for a good result.

modelVersions.name: Latin
modelVersions.description:
Very simple to use, just use the keywords, i advice to try with 1.3 weight in all keywords.

As i did in my generated images you can prompt somthing like "red dress" to have a colored one, it's not necessary a weight on it usually.

dance floor keyword is not necessary but can give a little context to the image.

Some of the images are generated using controlnet poses pack that you can find in my page.

Works also with anime.

modelVersions.name: Ballet
modelVersions.description:
This model is quite easy to use, just start your prompt with "a ballet dancer wearing ballet dress", add if you want "wearing tutu" and change the color as you want like "a ballet dancer wearing red ballet dress, wearing yellow tutu".

Keywords "in theater" and "in a studio" might give good results considering its a ballet dress and thats the proper environment for it.

regarding ballet corp keyword, i didn't manage to make it work even if many images of ballet corps dancing were used to train the model, you might give it a try and achieve what i didn't.

modelVersions.name: Belly Dance
modelVersions.description:
This model has been trained on images without background, it was my first time doing this and i discovered it is a bit problematic to generate the background you want.

My advice is to start your prompt with "a woman wearing belly dance dress" with a weight of the model of atleast 0.4, adviced 0.5 but it may give better results in the dress design till 0.8.

Then put a big weight to the kind of background you want, atleast 1.3. or as you will see in many of the images i posted with the model, you will get an empty background.

After this experience i strongly advice to always use images with background for LORA model trainings.

modelVersions.name: Samba
modelVersions.description:
This model has average difficulty to be used. You just have to play with weights to get what you want. You might want to give a weight to the keyword wearing samba dress dance, 1.2 or 1.3 might be good.

Also you might want to give a weight to the dress color, since it usually draw it in yellow and green.

Example "woman, (wearing samba dress dance:1.2), (red dress:1.2), etc"

carnival keyword doesn't always work, also in this case you might want to give an higher weight to make your woman inside a carnival party, but in most of the cases i tryied it wasn't necessary. carnival or carnival party both should work.
